<text top="217" left="512" width="316" height="14" font="7"><b>The President: </b>I take it that all the members of the</text>
<text top="235" left="481" width="347" height="14" font="1">Council have now voted, and I ask the Conference</text>
<text top="253" left="481" width="216" height="14" font="1">Officer to collect the ballot papers.</text>
<text top="289" left="628" width="8" height="14" font="1">*</text>
<text top="289" left="651" width="8" height="14" font="1">*</text>
<text top="289" left="673" width="8" height="14" font="1">*</text>
<text top="325" left="512" width="316" height="14" font="7"><b>The President: </b>All the ballot papers have been</text>
<text top="343" left="481" width="58" height="14" font="1">collected.</text>
<text top="379" left="512" width="316" height="14" font="1">The tellers will now count the ballots. There will be</text>
<text top="397" left="481" width="347" height="14" font="1">two independent countings of the ballots, one by each</text>
<text top="415" left="481" width="35" height="14" font="1">teller.</text>
<text top="451" left="628" width="8" height="14" font="1">*</text>
<text top="451" left="651" width="8" height="14" font="1">*</text>
<text top="451" left="673" width="8" height="14" font="1">*</text>
<text top="487" left="512" width="316" height="14" font="7"><b>The President: </b>The result of the voting is as</text>
<text top="505" left="481" width="49" height="14" font="1">follows:</text>
<text top="541" left="481" width="154" height="14" font="1">Number of ballot papers:</text>
<text top="541" left="813" width="15" height="14" font="1">15</text>
